On Thursday, May 22, 2003, at 02:14PM, Steve Sandlin <vwcarlocks(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>I use the correct tool for the job...line clamps.  They look a bit like vice 
>grips, but have flat, wide surfaces and a clamping mechanism.  They're 
>available at Sears Hardware, among other places.  I have a Sears pair, one 
>from Snap-On and another from Mac Tools.  All work well.
>Steve

I've bought some clamps from Stahlwille (SF12975). It's great for cutting off the flow of fuel before you open the line. It's hard to beat the economy of the golf tee or pencil but this works perfectly and stays put.

